# Linux Architecture Notes

## Linux Architecture

### 1. Kernel
- Core part of Linux OS
- Directly interacts with hardware
- Manages CPU, memory, devices, and processes

### 2. User Space
- Area where users and applications run
- Examples:
  - Bash
  - VS Code
  - Chrome
  - Linux commands

### 3. Init / systemd
- First process started after boot (PID 1)
- Manages system services and boot process
- Restarts failed services automatically

---

# Process Management

## What is a Process?
- A running program is called a process
- Every process has a PID (Process ID)

## Process States
- Running (R) → Using CPU
- Sleeping (S) → Waiting for input/resource
- Stopped (T) → Paused process
- Zombie (Z) → Finished but not cleaned

## Process Creation
- Processes are created using fork()
- Parent process creates child process

---

# What systemd Does

## Main Functions
- Starts services during boot
- Monitors background services
- Restarts failed services
- Handles logs using journald

## Useful Command
sudo systemctl status nginx

---

# 5 Daily Linux Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| ps aux | View running processes |
| top | Monitor CPU and memory |
| systemctl status | Check service status |
| journalctl -xe | View logs |
| kill PID | Stop a process |

